abstract: SAN FRANCISCO, Cal., Sept. 30. -- The Oceanic liner Alameda, Capt. Dodwell, bound for Honolulu with ninety-one passengers and an exceptionally valuable cargo, struck at 11:45 this morning on the jagged reef jutting out from Fort Point. abstract: The gross earnings of the Southern Railway Company for the year ended June 30 last were $48,145,108, an increase of $3,035,331 over those of the previous year. abstract: Apropos of "perfect rhymes," Mr. William T. Browne, in THE NEW YORK TIMES BOOK REVIEW, Oct. 7, has erred in but one of the rhymes he mentions. "Eclipse" cannot rhyme with "lips."
